h's Rude Truth--one of the first major studies of Roth's career as a whole--Ross Posnock examines Roth's "mature immaturity" in all its depth and richness. Philip Roth's Rude Truth will force readers to reconsider the narrow categories into which Roth has often been slotted--laureate of Newark, New Jersey; junior partner in the firm Salinger, Bellow, Mailer, and Malamud; Jewish-American regionalist. In dramatic contrast to these caricatures, the Roth who emerges from Posnock's readable and intellectually vibrant study is a great cosmopolitan in the tradition of Henry James and Milan Kundera.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066258008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Univ. Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311041343408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044250208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311045953140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400827343423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400827343.jpg  a978-3-11-041343-4  Princeton Univ. Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-044250-2  Princeton eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-045953-1  Princeton eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066258-0  PUP eBook-Package 2000-2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aPDA9PRIN